widgets_values:
Noise 1 = Remove most noise
Noise 0.01 = a lot of noise

Can be useful when backgrounds go wild on
highly-styled videos.

BG removal is based on the original video,
not styled video. Often, this is better
as the origin can be a green screen video. 
Styled videos also often merge outlines,
making bg removal less reliable.

nodes.title: Notes
widgets_values:
Lower Denoise  = Closer to the video, mouth movement, blink, face, etc
Higher Denoise = Better representation of the provided image

Lower ControlNet = Better representation of the provided image
Higher ControlNet = Closer to the video, mouth movement, blink, face, etc

Use decent face images.
Bypass groups to save VRAM.

Use different IPAdapters & weights for style changes
 - IP Adapter Light can be a good choice, even at weight 1!
 - Bypass "Image Crop Face" for non-face images

This will only swap photo-style faces - no video styles
will be applied. Will fail on non-photos.
